This paper deals with transfer learning in reinforcement learning, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The use of logic as a representation of high-level knowledge suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The focus on reinforcement learning and transfer learning suggests that it may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.RO (Robotics) sub-categories. The use of timed automata and temporal logic suggests that it may belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the use of propositional and first-order logic suggests that it may also belong to the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY, and cs.PL, in that order.
